title.narrative: OUTPUT 4.1: SOCIAL PROTECTION AND SOCIAL/ECONOMIC SECTORS

description.narrative: Output 4.1: Social service demand is strengthened through modelling of evidence-based linkages between social protection and social/economic sectors (including health, nutrition, protection, energy and HIV) in select counties, which contributes to Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 4 - Social inclusion: An increased number of children from the poorest & most vulnerable households benefit from shock- responsive & integrated social protection interventions, as well as from child-specific policies

title.narrative: Output 4.1: Social service demand is strengthened through modelling of evidence-based linkages between social protection and social/economic sectors (including health, nutrition, protection, energy and HIV) in select counties

description.narrative: UNICEF strengthened demand for social services through modelling of evidence-based linkages between Social Protection and Social-Economic sectors. This was done through supporting innovative county-led cash plus pilot programmes in the area of MNCH, Cash plus Energy and Nutrition-sensitive Social Protection, which significantly improved the overall delivery of the Inua Jamii programme. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
